17 /** Provides methods to compare types.
18  */
19 class TypeComparer(initctx: Context) extends DotClass with ConstraintHandling {
20   import TypeComparer._
21   implicit val ctx = initctx
22 
23   val state = ctx.typerState
24   import state.constraint
25 
26   private[this] var pendingSubTypes: mutable.Set[(Type, Type)] = null
27   private[this] var recCount = 0
28   private[this] var monitored = false
29 
30   private[this] var needsGc = false
31 
32   /** Is a subtype check in progress? In that case we may not
33    *  permanently instantiate type variables, because the corresponding
34    *  constraint might still be retracted and the instantiation should
35    *  then be reversed.
36    */
37   def subtypeCheckInProgress: Boolean = {
38     val result = recCount > 0
39     if (result) {
40       constr.println("*** needsGC ***")
41       needsGc = true
42     }
43     result
44   }
45 
46   /** For statistics: count how many isSubTypes are part of successful comparisons */
47   private[this] var successCount = 0
48   private[this] var totalCount = 0
49 
50   private[this] var myAnyClass: ClassSymbol = null
51   private[this] var myNothingClass: ClassSymbol = null
52   private[this] var myNullClass: ClassSymbol = null
53   private[this] var myPhantomNothingClass: ClassSymbol = null
54   private[this] var myObjectClass: ClassSymbol = null
55   private[this] var myAnyType: TypeRef = null
56   private[this] var myNothingType: TypeRef = null
57 
58   def AnyClass = {
59     if (myAnyClass == null) myAnyClass = defn.AnyClass
60     myAnyClass
61   }
62   def NothingClass = {
63     if (myNothingClass == null) myNothingClass = defn.NothingClass
64     myNothingClass
65   }
66   def NullClass = {
67     if (myNullClass == null) myNullClass = defn.NullClass
68     myNullClass
69   }
70   def PhantomNothingClass = {
71     if (myPhantomNothingClass == null) myPhantomNothingClass = defn.Phantom_NothingClass
72     myPhantomNothingClass
73   }
74   def ObjectClass = {
75     if (myObjectClass == null) myObjectClass = defn.ObjectClass
76     myObjectClass
77   }
78   def AnyType = {
79     if (myAnyType == null) myAnyType = AnyClass.typeRef
80     myAnyType
81   }
82   def NothingType = {
83     if (myNothingType == null) myNothingType = NothingClass.typeRef
84     myNothingType
85   }
86 
87   /** Indicates whether a previous subtype check used GADT bounds */
88   var GADTused = false
89 
90   /** Record that GADT bounds of `sym` were used in a subtype check.
91    *  But exclude constructor type parameters, as these are aliased
92    *  to the corresponding class parameters, which does not constitute
93    *  a true usage of a GADT symbol.
94    */
95   private def GADTusage(sym: Symbol) = {
96     if (!sym.owner.isConstructor) GADTused = true
97     true
98   }
99 
100   // Subtype testing `<:<`
101 
102   def topLevelSubType(tp1: Type, tp2: Type): Boolean = {
103     if (tp2 eq NoType) return false
104     if ((tp2 eq tp1) || (tp2 eq WildcardType)) return true
105     try isSubType(tp1, tp2)
106     finally {
107       monitored = false
108       if (Config.checkConstraintsSatisfiable)
109         assert(isSatisfiable, constraint.show)
110     }
111   }
112 
113   private[this] var approx: ApproxState = NoApprox
114   protected def approxState = approx
115 
116   protected def isSubType(tp1: Type, tp2: Type, a: ApproxState): Boolean = {
117     val saved = approx
118     this.approx = a
119     try recur(tp1, tp2) finally this.approx = saved
120   }
121 
122   protected def isSubType(tp1: Type, tp2: Type): Boolean = isSubType(tp1, tp2, NoApprox)
123 
124   protected def recur(tp1: Type, tp2: Type): Boolean = trace(s"isSubType ${traceInfo(tp1, tp2)} $approx", subtyping) {
125 
126     def monitoredIsSubType = {
127       if (pendingSubTypes == null) {
128         pendingSubTypes = new mutable.HashSet[(Type, Type)]
129         ctx.log(s"!!! deep subtype recursion involving ${tp1.show} <:< ${tp2.show}, constraint = ${state.constraint.show}")
130         ctx.log(s"!!! constraint = ${constraint.show}")
131         //if (ctx.settings.YnoDeepSubtypes.value) {
132         //  new Error("deep subtype").printStackTrace()
133         //}
134         assert(!ctx.settings.YnoDeepSubtypes.value)
135         if (Config.traceDeepSubTypeRecursions && !this.isInstanceOf[ExplainingTypeComparer])
136           ctx.log(TypeComparer.explained(implicit ctx => ctx.typeComparer.isSubType(tp1, tp2, approx)))
137       }
138       // Eliminate LazyRefs before checking whether we have seen a type before
139       val normalize = new TypeMap {
140         val DerefLimit = 10
141         var derefCount = 0
142         def apply(t: Type) = t match {
143           case t: LazyRef =>
144             // Dereference a lazyref to detect underlying matching types, but
145             // be careful not to get into an infinite recursion. If recursion count
146             // exceeds `DerefLimit`, approximate with `NoType` instead.
147             derefCount += 1
148             if (derefCount >= DerefLimit) NoType
149             else try mapOver(t.ref) finally derefCount -= 1
150           case _ =>
151             mapOver(t)
152         }
153       }
154       val p = (normalize(tp1), normalize(tp2))
155       !pendingSubTypes(p) && {
156         try {
157           pendingSubTypes += p
158           firstTry
159         } finally {
160           pendingSubTypes -= p
161         }
162       }
163     }
164 
165     def firstTry: Boolean = tp2 match {
166       case tp2: NamedType =>
167         def compareNamed(tp1: Type, tp2: NamedType): Boolean = {
168           implicit val ctx = this.ctx
169           tp2.info match {
170             case info2: TypeAlias => recur(tp1, info2.alias)
171             case _ => tp1 match {
172               case tp1: NamedType =>
173                 tp1.info match {
174                   case info1: TypeAlias =>
175                     if (recur(info1.alias, tp2)) return true
176                     if (tp1.prefix.isStable) return false
177                       // If tp1.prefix is stable, the alias does contain all information about the original ref, so
178                       // there's no need to try something else. (This is important for performance).
179                       // To see why we cannot in general stop here, consider:
180                       //
181                       //     trait C { type A }
182                       //     trait D { type A = String }
183                       //     (C & D)#A <: C#A
184                       //
185                       // Following the alias leads to the judgment `String <: C#A` which is false.
186                       // However the original judgment should be true.
187                   case _ =>
188                 }
189                 val sym2 = tp2.symbol
190                 var sym1 = tp1.symbol
191                 if (sym1.is(ModuleClass) && sym2.is(ModuleVal))
192                   // For convenience we want X$ <:< X.type
193                   // This is safe because X$ self-type is X.type
194                   sym1 = sym1.companionModule
195                 if ((sym1 ne NoSymbol) && (sym1 eq sym2))
196                   ctx.erasedTypes ||
197                   sym1.isStaticOwner ||
198                   isSubType(tp1.prefix, tp2.prefix) ||
199                   thirdTryNamed(tp2)
200                 else
201                   (  (tp1.name eq tp2.name)
202                   && tp1.isMemberRef
203                   && tp2.isMemberRef
204                   && isSubType(tp1.prefix, tp2.prefix)
205                   && tp1.signature == tp2.signature
206                   && !(sym1.isClass && sym2.isClass)  // class types don't subtype each other
207                   ) ||
208                   thirdTryNamed(tp2)
209               case _ =>
210                 secondTry
211             }
212           }
213         }
214         compareNamed(tp1, tp2)
215       case tp2: ProtoType =>
216         isMatchedByProto(tp2, tp1)
217       case tp2: BoundType =>
218         tp2 == tp1 || secondTry
219       case tp2: TypeVar =>
220         recur(tp1, tp2.underlying)
221       case tp2: WildcardType =>
222         def compareWild = tp2.optBounds match {
223           case TypeBounds(_, hi) => recur(tp1, hi)
224           case NoType => true
225         }
226         compareWild
227       case tp2: LazyRef =>
228         !tp2.evaluating && recur(tp1, tp2.ref)
229       case tp2: AnnotatedType =>
230         recur(tp1, tp2.tpe) // todo: refine?
231       case tp2: ThisType =>
232         def compareThis = {
233           val cls2 = tp2.cls
234           tp1 match {
235             case tp1: ThisType =>
236               // We treat two prefixes A.this, B.this as equivalent if
237               // A's selftype derives from B and B's selftype derives from A.
238               val cls1 = tp1.cls
239               cls1.classInfo.selfType.derivesFrom(cls2) &&
240               cls2.classInfo.selfType.derivesFrom(cls1)
241             case tp1: NamedType if cls2.is(Module) && cls2.eq(tp1.widen.typeSymbol) =>
242               cls2.isStaticOwner ||
243               recur(tp1.prefix, cls2.owner.thisType) ||
244               secondTry
245             case _ =>
246               secondTry
247           }
248         }
249         compareThis
250       case tp2: SuperType =>
251         def compareSuper = tp1 match {
252           case tp1: SuperType =>
253             isSubType(tp1.thistpe, tp2.thistpe) &&
254             isSameType(tp1.supertpe, tp2.supertpe)
255           case _ =>
256             secondTry
257         }
258         compareSuper
259       case AndType(tp21, tp22) =>
260         recur(tp1, tp21) && recur(tp1, tp22)
261       case OrType(tp21, tp22) =>
262         if (tp21.stripTypeVar eq tp22.stripTypeVar) recur(tp1, tp21)
263         else secondTry
264       case TypeErasure.ErasedValueType(tycon1, underlying2) =>
265         def compareErasedValueType = tp1 match {
266           case TypeErasure.ErasedValueType(tycon2, underlying1) =>
267             (tycon1.symbol eq tycon2.symbol) && isSameType(underlying1, underlying2)
268           case _ =>
269             secondTry
270         }
271         compareErasedValueType
272       case ConstantType(v2) =>
273         tp1 match {
274           case ConstantType(v1) => v1.value == v2.value
275           case _ => secondTry
276         }
277       case _: FlexType =>
278         true
279       case _ =>
280         secondTry
281     }
282 
283     def secondTry: Boolean = tp1 match {
284       case tp1: NamedType =>
285         tp1.info match {
286           case info1: TypeAlias =>
287             if (recur(info1.alias, tp2)) return true
288             if (tp1.prefix.isStable) return false
289           case _ =>
290             if (tp1 eq NothingType) return tp1 == tp2.bottomType
291         }
292         thirdTry
293       case tp1: TypeParamRef =>
294         def flagNothingBound = {
295           if (!frozenConstraint && tp2.isRef(defn.NothingClass) && state.isGlobalCommittable) {
296             def msg = s"!!! instantiated to Nothing: $tp1, constraint = ${constraint.show}"
297             if (Config.failOnInstantiationToNothing) assert(false, msg)
298             else ctx.log(msg)
299           }
300           true
301         }
302         def compareTypeParamRef =
303           ctx.mode.is(Mode.TypevarsMissContext) ||
304           isSubTypeWhenFrozen(bounds(tp1).hi, tp2) || {
305             if (canConstrain(tp1) && !approx.high)
306               addConstraint(tp1, tp2, fromBelow = false) && flagNothingBound
307             else thirdTry
308           }
309         compareTypeParamRef
310       case tp1: ThisType =>
311         val cls1 = tp1.cls
312         tp2 match {
313           case tp2: TermRef if cls1.is(Module) && cls1.eq(tp2.widen.typeSymbol) =>
314             cls1.isStaticOwner ||
315             recur(cls1.owner.thisType, tp2.prefix) ||
316             thirdTry
317           case _ =>
318             thirdTry
319         }
320       case tp1: SkolemType =>
321         tp2 match {
322           case tp2: SkolemType if !ctx.phase.isTyper && isSubType(tp1.info, tp2.info) => true
323           case _ => thirdTry
324         }
325       case tp1: TypeVar =>
326         recur(tp1.underlying, tp2)
327       case tp1: WildcardType =>
328         def compareWild = tp1.optBounds match {
329           case TypeBounds(lo, _) => recur(lo, tp2)
330           case _ => true
331         }
332         compareWild
333       case tp1: LazyRef =>
334         // If `tp1` is in train of being evaluated, don't force it
335         // because that would cause an assertionError. Return false instead.
336         // See i859.scala for an example where we hit this case.
337         !tp1.evaluating && recur(tp1.ref, tp2)
338       case tp1: AnnotatedType =>
339         recur(tp1.tpe, tp2)
340       case AndType(tp11, tp12) =>
341         if (tp11.stripTypeVar eq tp12.stripTypeVar) recur(tp11, tp2)
342         else thirdTry
343       case tp1 @ OrType(tp11, tp12) =>
344         def joinOK = tp2.dealias match {
345           case tp2: AppliedType if !tp2.tycon.typeSymbol.isClass =>
346             // If we apply the default algorithm for `A[X] | B[Y] <: C[Z]` where `C` is a
347             // type parameter, we will instantiate `C` to `A` and then fail when comparing
348             // with `B[Y]`. To do the right thing, we need to instantiate `C` to the
349             // common superclass of `A` and `B`.
350             recur(tp1.join, tp2)
351           case _ =>
352             false
353         }
354         joinOK || recur(tp11, tp2) && recur(tp12, tp2)
355       case _: FlexType =>
356         true
357       case _ =>
358         thirdTry
359     }
360 
361     def thirdTryNamed(tp2: NamedType): Boolean = tp2.info match {
362       case TypeBounds(lo2, _) =>
363         def compareGADT: Boolean = {
364           val gbounds2 = ctx.gadt.bounds(tp2.symbol)
365           (gbounds2 != null) &&
366             (isSubTypeWhenFrozen(tp1, gbounds2.lo) ||
367               narrowGADTBounds(tp2, tp1, approx, isUpper = false)) &&
368             GADTusage(tp2.symbol)
369         }
370         isSubApproxHi(tp1, lo2) || compareGADT || fourthTry
371 
372       case _ =>
373         val cls2 = tp2.symbol
374         if (cls2.isClass) {
375           if (cls2.typeParams.nonEmpty && tp1.isHK)
376             recur(tp1, EtaExpansion(cls2.typeRef))
377           else {
378             val base = tp1.baseType(cls2)
379             if (base.exists) {
380               if (cls2.is(JavaDefined))
381                 // If `cls2` is parameterized, we are seeing a raw type, so we need to compare only the symbol
382                 return base.typeSymbol == cls2
383               if (base ne tp1)
384                 return isSubType(base, tp2, if (tp1.isRef(cls2)) approx else approx.addLow)
385             }
386             if (cls2 == defn.SingletonClass && tp1.isStable) return true
387           }
388         }
389         fourthTry
390     }
391 
392     def thirdTry: Boolean = tp2 match {
393       case tp2 @ AppliedType(tycon2, args2) =>
394         compareAppliedType2(tp2, tycon2, args2)
395       case tp2: NamedType =>
396         thirdTryNamed(tp2)
397       case tp2: TypeParamRef =>
398         def compareTypeParamRef =
399           (ctx.mode is Mode.TypevarsMissContext) || {
400           val alwaysTrue =
401             // The following condition is carefully formulated to catch all cases
402             // where the subtype relation is true without needing to add a constraint
403             // It's tricky because we might need to either approximate tp2 by its
404             // lower bound or else widen tp1 and check that the result is a subtype of tp2.
405             // So if the constraint is not yet frozen, we do the same comparison again
406             // with a frozen constraint, which means that we get a chance to do the
407             // widening in `fourthTry` before adding to the constraint.
408             if (frozenConstraint) isSubType(tp1, bounds(tp2).lo)
409             else isSubTypeWhenFrozen(tp1, tp2)
410           alwaysTrue || {
411             if (canConstrain(tp2) && !approx.low)
412               addConstraint(tp2, tp1.widenExpr, fromBelow = true)
413             else fourthTry
414           }
415         }
416         compareTypeParamRef
417       case tp2: RefinedType =>
418         def compareRefinedSlow: Boolean = {
419           val name2 = tp2.refinedName
420           recur(tp1, tp2.parent) &&
421             (name2 == nme.WILDCARD || hasMatchingMember(name2, tp1, tp2))
422         }
423         def compareRefined: Boolean = {
424           val tp1w = tp1.widen
425           val skipped2 = skipMatching(tp1w, tp2)
426           if ((skipped2 eq tp2) || !Config.fastPathForRefinedSubtype)
427             tp1 match {
428               case tp1: AndType =>
429                 // Delay calling `compareRefinedSlow` because looking up a member
430                 // of an `AndType` can lead to a cascade of subtyping checks
431                 // This twist is needed to make collection/generic/ParFactory.scala compile
432                 fourthTry || compareRefinedSlow
433               case tp1: HKTypeLambda =>
434                 // HKTypeLambdas do not have members.
435                 fourthTry
436               case _ =>
437                 compareRefinedSlow || fourthTry
438             }
439           else // fast path, in particular for refinements resulting from parameterization.
440             isSubRefinements(tp1w.asInstanceOf[RefinedType], tp2, skipped2) &&
441             recur(tp1, skipped2)
442         }
443         compareRefined
444       case tp2: RecType =>
445         def compareRec = tp1.safeDealias match {
446           case tp1: RecType =>
447             val rthis1 = tp1.recThis
448             recur(tp1.parent, tp2.parent.substRecThis(tp2, rthis1))
449           case _ =>
450             val tp1stable = ensureStableSingleton(tp1)
451             recur(fixRecs(tp1stable, tp1stable.widenExpr), tp2.parent.substRecThis(tp2, tp1stable))
452         }
453         compareRec
454       case tp2: HKTypeLambda =>
455         def compareTypeLambda: Boolean = tp1.stripTypeVar match {
456           case tp1: HKTypeLambda =>
457             /* Don't compare bounds of lambdas under language:Scala2, or t2994 will fail.
458             * The issue is that, logically, bounds should compare contravariantly,
459             * but that would invalidate a pattern exploited in t2994:
460             *
461             *    [X0 <: Number] -> Number   <:<    [X0] -> Any
462             *
463             * Under the new scheme, `[X0] -> Any` is NOT a kind that subsumes
464             * all other bounds. You'd have to write `[X0 >: Any <: Nothing] -> Any` instead.
465             * This might look weird, but is the only logically correct way to do it.
466             *
467             * Note: it would be nice if this could trigger a migration warning, but I
468             * am not sure how, since the code is buried so deep in subtyping logic.
469             */
470             def boundsOK =
471               ctx.scala2Mode ||
472               tp1.typeParams.corresponds(tp2.typeParams)((tparam1, tparam2) =>
473                 isSubType(tparam2.paramInfo.subst(tp2, tp1), tparam1.paramInfo))
474             val saved = comparedTypeLambdas
475             comparedTypeLambdas += tp1
476             comparedTypeLambdas += tp2
477             try
478               variancesConform(tp1.typeParams, tp2.typeParams) &&
479               boundsOK &&
480               isSubType(tp1.resType, tp2.resType.subst(tp2, tp1))
481             finally comparedTypeLambdas = saved
482           case _ =>
483             if (tp1.isHK) {
484               val tparams1 = tp1.typeParams
485               return recur(
486                 HKTypeLambda.fromParams(tparams1, tp1.appliedTo(tparams1.map(_.paramRef))),
487                 tp2
488               )
489             }
490             else tp2 match {
491               case EtaExpansion(tycon2) if tycon2.symbol.isClass =>
492                 return recur(tp1, tycon2)
493               case _ =>
494             }
495             fourthTry
496         }
497         compareTypeLambda
498       case OrType(tp21, tp22) =>
499         val tp1a = tp1.widenDealias
500         if (tp1a ne tp1)
501           // Follow the alias; this might avoid truncating the search space in the either below
502           // Note that it's safe to widen here because singleton types cannot be part of `|`.
503           return recur(tp1a, tp2)
504 
505         // Rewrite T1 <: (T211 & T212) | T22 to T1 <: (T211 | T22) and T1 <: (T212 | T22)
506         // and analogously for T1 <: T21 | (T221 & T222)
507         // `|' types to the right of <: are problematic, because
508         // we have to choose one constraint set or another, which might cut off
509         // solutions. The rewriting delays the point where we have to choose.
510         tp21 match {
511           case AndType(tp211, tp212) =>
512             return recur(tp1, OrType(tp211, tp22)) && recur(tp1, OrType(tp212, tp22))
513           case _ =>
514         }
515         tp22 match {
516           case AndType(tp221, tp222) =>
517             return recur(tp1, OrType(tp21, tp221)) && recur(tp1, OrType(tp21, tp222))
518           case _ =>
519         }
520         either(recur(tp1, tp21), recur(tp1, tp22)) || fourthTry
521       case tp2: MethodOrPoly =>
522         def compareMethod = tp1 match {
523           case tp1: MethodOrPoly =>
524             (tp1.signature consistentParams tp2.signature) &&
525               matchingParams(tp1, tp2) &&
526               (!tp2.isImplicitMethod || tp1.isImplicitMethod) &&
527               isSubType(tp1.resultType, tp2.resultType.subst(tp2, tp1))
528           case _ =>
529             false
530         }
531         compareMethod
532       case tp2 @ ExprType(restpe2) =>
533         def compareExpr = tp1 match {
534           // We allow ()T to be a subtype of => T.
535           // We need some subtype relationship between them so that e.g.
536           // def toString   and   def toString()   don't clash when seen
537           // as members of the same type. And it seems most logical to take
538           // ()T <:< => T, since everything one can do with a => T one can
539           // also do with a ()T by automatic () insertion.
540           case tp1 @ MethodType(Nil) => isSubType(tp1.resultType, restpe2)
541           case _ => isSubType(tp1.widenExpr, restpe2)
542         }
543         compareExpr
544       case tp2 @ TypeBounds(lo2, hi2) =>
545         def compareTypeBounds = tp1 match {
546           case tp1 @ TypeBounds(lo1, hi1) =>
547             ((lo2 eq NothingType) || isSubType(lo2, lo1)) &&
548             ((hi2 eq AnyType) || isSubType(hi1, hi2))
549           case tp1: ClassInfo =>
550             tp2 contains tp1
551           case _ =>
552             false
553         }
554         compareTypeBounds
555       case ClassInfo(pre2, cls2, _, _, _) =>
556         def compareClassInfo = tp1 match {
557           case ClassInfo(pre1, cls1, _, _, _) =>
558             (cls1 eq cls2) && isSubType(pre1, pre2)
559           case _ =>
560             false
561         }
562         compareClassInfo
563       case _ =>
564         fourthTry
565     }
566 
567     def fourthTry: Boolean = tp1 match {
568       case tp1: TypeRef =>
569         tp1.info match {
570           case TypeBounds(_, hi1) =>
571             def compareGADT = {
572               val gbounds1 = ctx.gadt.bounds(tp1.symbol)
573               (gbounds1 != null) &&
574                 (isSubTypeWhenFrozen(gbounds1.hi, tp2) ||
575                 narrowGADTBounds(tp1, tp2, approx, isUpper = true)) &&
576                 GADTusage(tp1.symbol)
577             }
578             isSubType(hi1, tp2, approx.addLow) || compareGADT
579           case _ =>
580             def isNullable(tp: Type): Boolean = tp.widenDealias match {
581               case tp: TypeRef => tp.symbol.isNullableClass
582               case tp: RefinedOrRecType => isNullable(tp.parent)
583               case tp: AppliedType => isNullable(tp.tycon)
584               case AndType(tp1, tp2) => isNullable(tp1) && isNullable(tp2)
585               case OrType(tp1, tp2) => isNullable(tp1) || isNullable(tp2)
586               case _ => false
587             }
588             val sym1 = tp1.symbol
589             (sym1 eq NothingClass) && tp2.isValueTypeOrLambda && !tp2.isPhantom ||
590             (sym1 eq NullClass) && isNullable(tp2) ||
591             (sym1 eq PhantomNothingClass) && tp1.topType == tp2.topType
592         }
593       case tp1 @ AppliedType(tycon1, args1) =>
594         compareAppliedType1(tp1, tycon1, args1)
595       case tp1: SingletonType =>
596         /** if `tp2 == p.type` and `p: q.type` then try `tp1 <:< q.type` as a last effort.*/
597         def comparePaths = tp2 match {
598           case tp2: TermRef =>
599             tp2.info.widenExpr.dealias match {
600               case tp2i: SingletonType =>
601                 recur(tp1, tp2i)
602                   // see z1720.scala for a case where this can arise even in typer.
603                   // Also, i1753.scala, to show why the dealias above is necessary.
604               case _ => false
605             }
606           case _ =>
607             false
608         }
609         isNewSubType(tp1.underlying.widenExpr) || comparePaths
610       case tp1: RefinedType =>
611         isNewSubType(tp1.parent)
612       case tp1: RecType =>
613         isNewSubType(tp1.parent)
614       case tp1: HKTypeLambda =>
615         def compareHKLambda = tp1 match {
616           case EtaExpansion(tycon1) => recur(tycon1, tp2)
617           case _ => tp2 match {
618             case tp2: HKTypeLambda => false // this case was covered in thirdTry
619             case _ => tp2.isHK && isSubType(tp1.resultType, tp2.appliedTo(tp1.paramRefs))
620           }
621         }
622         compareHKLambda
623       case AndType(tp11, tp12) =>
624         val tp2a = tp2.dealias
625         if (tp2a ne tp2) // Follow the alias; this might avoid truncating the search space in the either below
626           return recur(tp1, tp2a)
627 
628         // Rewrite (T111 | T112) & T12 <: T2 to (T111 & T12) <: T2 and (T112 | T12) <: T2
629         // and analogously for T11 & (T121 | T122) & T12 <: T2
630         // `&' types to the left of <: are problematic, because
631         // we have to choose one constraint set or another, which might cut off
632         // solutions. The rewriting delays the point where we have to choose.
633         tp11 match {
634           case OrType(tp111, tp112) =>
635             return recur(AndType(tp111, tp12), tp2) && recur(AndType(tp112, tp12), tp2)
636           case _ =>
637         }
638         tp12 match {
639           case OrType(tp121, tp122) =>
640             return recur(AndType(tp11, tp121), tp2) && recur(AndType(tp11, tp122), tp2)
641           case _ =>
642         }
643         either(recur(tp11, tp2), recur(tp12, tp2))
644       case JavaArrayType(elem1) =>
645         def compareJavaArray = tp2 match {
646           case JavaArrayType(elem2) => isSubType(elem1, elem2)
647           case _ => tp2 isRef ObjectClass
648         }
649         compareJavaArray
650       case tp1: ExprType if ctx.phase.id > ctx.gettersPhase.id =>
651         // getters might have converted T to => T, need to compensate.
652         recur(tp1.widenExpr, tp2)
653       case _ =>
654         false
655     }
656 
657     /** Subtype test for the hk application `tp2 = tycon2[args2]`.
658     */
659     def compareAppliedType2(tp2: AppliedType, tycon2: Type, args2: List[Type]): Boolean = {
660       val tparams = tycon2.typeParams
661       if (tparams.isEmpty) return false // can happen for ill-typed programs, e.g. neg/tcpoly_overloaded.scala
662 
663       /** True if `tp1` and `tp2` have compatible type constructors and their
664       *  corresponding arguments are subtypes relative to their variance (see `isSubArgs`).
665       */
666       def isMatchingApply(tp1: Type): Boolean = tp1 match {
667         case AppliedType(tycon1, args1) =>
668           tycon1.dealias match {
669             case tycon1: TypeParamRef =>
670               (tycon1 == tycon2 ||
671               canConstrain(tycon1) && tryInstantiate(tycon1, tycon2)) &&
672               isSubArgs(args1, args2, tp1, tparams)
673             case tycon1: TypeRef =>
674               tycon2.dealias match {
675                 case tycon2: TypeRef if tycon1.symbol == tycon2.symbol =>
676                   isSubType(tycon1.prefix, tycon2.prefix) &&
677                   isSubArgs(args1, args2, tp1, tparams)
678                 case _ =>
679                   false
680               }
681             case tycon1: TypeVar =>
682               isMatchingApply(tycon1.underlying)
683             case tycon1: AnnotatedType =>
684               isMatchingApply(tycon1.underlying)
685             case _ =>
686               false
687           }
688         case _ =>
689           false
690       }
691 
692       /** `param2` can be instantiated to a type application prefix of the LHS
693       *  or to a type application prefix of one of the LHS base class instances
694       *  and the resulting type application is a supertype of `tp1`,
695       *  or fallback to fourthTry.
696       */
697       def canInstantiate(tycon2: TypeParamRef): Boolean = {
698 
699         /** Let
700         *
701         *    `tparams_1, ..., tparams_k-1`    be the type parameters of the rhs
702         *    `tparams1_1, ..., tparams1_n-1`  be the type parameters of the constructor of the lhs
703         *    `args1_1, ..., args1_n-1`        be the type arguments of the lhs
704         *    `d  =  n - k`
705         *
706         *  Returns `true` iff `d >= 0` and `tycon2` can be instantiated to
707         *
708         *      [tparams1_d, ... tparams1_n-1] -> tycon1[args_1, ..., args_d-1, tparams_d, ... tparams_n-1]
709         *
710         *  such that the resulting type application is a supertype of `tp1`.
711         */
712         def appOK(tp1base: Type) = tp1base match {
713           case tp1base: AppliedType =>
714             var tycon1 = tp1base.tycon
715             val args1 = tp1base.args
716             val tparams1all = tycon1.typeParams
717             val lengthDiff = tparams1all.length - tparams.length
718             lengthDiff >= 0 && {
719               val tparams1 = tparams1all.drop(lengthDiff)
720               variancesConform(tparams1, tparams) && {
721                 if (lengthDiff > 0)
722                   tycon1 = HKTypeLambda(tparams1.map(_.paramName))(
723                     tl => tparams1.map(tparam => tl.integrate(tparams, tparam.paramInfo).bounds),
724                     tl => tp1base.tycon.appliedTo(args1.take(lengthDiff) ++
725                             tparams1.indices.toList.map(tl.paramRefs(_))))
726                 (ctx.mode.is(Mode.TypevarsMissContext) ||
727                   tryInstantiate(tycon2, tycon1.ensureHK)) &&
728                   recur(tp1, tycon1.appliedTo(args2))
729               }
730             }
731           case _ => false
732         }
733 
734         tp1.widen match {
735           case tp1w: AppliedType => appOK(tp1w)
736           case tp1w =>
737             tp1w.typeSymbol.isClass && {
738               val classBounds = tycon2.classSymbols
739               def liftToBase(bcs: List[ClassSymbol]): Boolean = bcs match {
740                 case bc :: bcs1 =>
741                   classBounds.exists(bc.derivesFrom) && appOK(tp1w.baseType(bc)) ||
742                   liftToBase(bcs1)
743                 case _ =>
744                   false
745               }
746               liftToBase(tp1w.baseClasses)
747             } ||
748             fourthTry
749         }
750       }
751 
752       /** Fall back to comparing either with `fourthTry` or against the lower
753       *  approximation of the rhs.
754       *  @param   tyconLo   The type constructor's lower approximation.
755       */
756       def fallback(tyconLo: Type) =
757         either(fourthTry, isSubApproxHi(tp1, tyconLo.applyIfParameterized(args2)))
758 
759       /** Let `tycon2bounds` be the bounds of the RHS type constructor `tycon2`.
760       *  Let `app2 = tp2` where the type constructor of `tp2` is replaced by
761       *  `tycon2bounds.lo`.
762       *  If both bounds are the same, continue with `tp1 <:< app2`.
763       *  otherwise continue with either
764       *
765       *    tp1 <:< tp2    using fourthTry (this might instantiate params in tp1)
766       *    tp1 <:< app2   using isSubType (this might instantiate params in tp2)
767       */
768       def compareLower(tycon2bounds: TypeBounds, tyconIsTypeRef: Boolean): Boolean =
769         if (tycon2bounds.lo eq tycon2bounds.hi)
770           if (tyconIsTypeRef) recur(tp1, tp2.superType)
771           else isSubApproxHi(tp1, tycon2bounds.lo.applyIfParameterized(args2))
772         else
773           fallback(tycon2bounds.lo)
774 
775       tycon2 match {
776         case param2: TypeParamRef =>
777           isMatchingApply(tp1) ||
778           canConstrain(param2) && canInstantiate(param2) ||
779           compareLower(bounds(param2), tyconIsTypeRef = false)
780         case tycon2: TypeRef =>
781           isMatchingApply(tp1) || {
782             tycon2.info match {
783               case info2: TypeBounds =>
784                 compareLower(info2, tyconIsTypeRef = true)
785               case info2: ClassInfo =>
786                 val base = tp1.baseType(info2.cls)
787                 if (base.exists && base.ne(tp1))
788                   isSubType(base, tp2, if (tp1.isRef(info2.cls)) approx else approx.addLow)
789                 else fourthTry
790               case _ =>
791                 fourthTry
792             }
793           }
794         case _: TypeVar | _: AnnotatedType =>
795           recur(tp1, tp2.superType)
796         case tycon2: AppliedType =>
797           fallback(tycon2.lowerBound)
798         case _ =>
799           false
800       }
801     }
802 
803     /** Subtype test for the application `tp1 = tycon1[args1]`.
804     */
805     def compareAppliedType1(tp1: AppliedType, tycon1: Type, args1: List[Type]): Boolean =
806       tycon1 match {
807         case param1: TypeParamRef =>
808           def canInstantiate = tp2 match {
809             case AppliedType(tycon2, args2) =>
810               tryInstantiate(param1, tycon2.ensureHK) && isSubArgs(args1, args2, tp1, tycon2.typeParams)
811             case _ =>
812               false
813           }
814           canConstrain(param1) && canInstantiate ||
815             isSubType(bounds(param1).hi.applyIfParameterized(args1), tp2, approx.addLow)
816         case tycon1: TypeRef if tycon1.symbol.isClass =>
817           false
818         case tycon1: TypeProxy =>
819           recur(tp1.superType, tp2)
820         case _ =>
821           false
822       }
823 
824     /** Like tp1 <:< tp2, but returns false immediately if we know that
825     *  the case was covered previously during subtyping.
826     */
827     def isNewSubType(tp1: Type): Boolean =
828       if (isCovered(tp1) && isCovered(tp2)) {
829         //println(s"useless subtype: $tp1 <:< $tp2")
830         false
831       } else isSubType(tp1, tp2, approx.addLow)
832 
833     def isSubApproxHi(tp1: Type, tp2: Type): Boolean =
834       (tp2 ne NothingType) && isSubType(tp1, tp2, approx.addHigh)
835 
836     // begin recur
837     if (tp2 eq NoType) false
838     else if (tp1 eq tp2) true
839     else {
840       val saved = constraint
841       val savedSuccessCount = successCount
842       try {
843         recCount = recCount + 1
844         if (recCount >= Config.LogPendingSubTypesThreshold) monitored = true
845         val result = if (monitored) monitoredIsSubType else firstTry
846         recCount = recCount - 1
847         if (!result) state.resetConstraintTo(saved)
848         else if (recCount == 0 && needsGc) {
849           state.gc()
850           needsGc = false
851         }
852         if (Stats.monitored) recordStatistics(result, savedSuccessCount)
853         result
854       } catch {
855         case NonFatal(ex) =>
856           if (ex.isInstanceOf[AssertionError]) showGoal(tp1, tp2)
857           recCount -= 1
858           state.resetConstraintTo(saved)
859           successCount = savedSuccessCount
860           throw ex
861       }
862     }
863   }
864 
865   /** Subtype test for corresponding arguments in `args1`, `args2` according to
866   *  variances in type parameters `tparams`.
867   */
868   def isSubArgs(args1: List[Type], args2: List[Type], tp1: Type, tparams: List[ParamInfo]): Boolean =
869     if (args1.isEmpty) args2.isEmpty
870     else args2.nonEmpty && {
871       val tparam = tparams.head
872       val v = tparam.paramVariance
873 
874       def compareCaptured(arg1: Type, arg2: Type): Boolean = arg1 match {
875         case arg1: TypeBounds =>
876           val captured = TypeRef(tp1, tparam.asInstanceOf[TypeSymbol])
877           isSubArg(captured, arg2)
878         case _ =>
879           false
880       }
881 
882       def isSubArg(arg1: Type, arg2: Type): Boolean = arg2 match {
883         case arg2: TypeBounds =>
884           arg2.contains(arg1) || compareCaptured(arg1, arg2)
885         case _ =>
886           arg1 match {
887             case arg1: TypeBounds =>
888               compareCaptured(arg1, arg2)
889             case _ =>
890               (v > 0 || isSubType(arg2, arg1)) &&
891               (v < 0 || isSubType(arg1, arg2))
892           }
893       }
894 
895       val arg1 = args1.head
896       val arg2 = args2.head
897       isSubArg(arg1, arg2) || {
898         // last effort: try to adapt variances of higher-kinded types if this is sound.
899         // TODO: Move this to eta-expansion?
900         val adapted2 = arg2.adaptHkVariances(tparam.paramInfo)
901         adapted2.ne(arg2) && isSubArg(arg1, adapted2)
902       }
903     } && isSubArgs(args1.tail, args2.tail, tp1, tparams.tail)
904 
905   /** Test whether `tp1` has a base type of the form `B[T1, ..., Tn]` where
906    *   - `B` derives from one of the class symbols of `tp2`,
907    *   - the type parameters of `B` match one-by-one the variances of `tparams`,
908    *   - `B` satisfies predicate `p`.
909    */
910   private def testLifted(tp1: Type, tp2: Type, tparams: List[TypeParamInfo], p: Type => Boolean): Boolean = {
911     val classBounds = tp2.classSymbols
912     def recur(bcs: List[ClassSymbol]): Boolean = bcs match {
913       case bc :: bcs1 =>
914         (classBounds.exists(bc.derivesFrom) &&
915           variancesConform(bc.typeParams, tparams) &&
916           p(tp1.baseType(bc))
917         ||
918         recur(bcs1))
919       case nil =>
920         false
921     }
922     recur(tp1.baseClasses)
923   }
924 
925   /** Replace any top-level recursive type `{ z => T }` in `tp` with
926    *  `[z := anchor]T`.
927    */
928   private def fixRecs(anchor: SingletonType, tp: Type): Type = {
929     def fix(tp: Type): Type = tp.stripTypeVar match {
930       case tp: RecType => fix(tp.parent).substRecThis(tp, anchor)
931       case tp @ RefinedType(parent, rname, rinfo) => tp.derivedRefinedType(fix(parent), rname, rinfo)
932       case tp: TypeParamRef => fixOrElse(bounds(tp).hi, tp)
933       case tp: TypeProxy => fixOrElse(tp.underlying, tp)
934       case tp: AndOrType => tp.derivedAndOrType(fix(tp.tp1), fix(tp.tp2))
935       case tp => tp
936     }
937     def fixOrElse(tp: Type, fallback: Type) = {
938       val tp1 = fix(tp)
939       if (tp1 ne tp) tp1 else fallback
940     }
941     fix(tp)
942   }
943 
944   /** Returns true iff the result of evaluating either `op1` or `op2` is true,
945    *  trying at the same time to keep the constraint as wide as possible.
946    *  E.g, if
947    *
948    *    tp11 <:< tp12 = true   with post-constraint c1
949    *    tp12 <:< tp22 = true   with post-constraint c2
950    *
951    *  and c1 subsumes c2, then c2 is kept as the post-constraint of the result,
952    *  otherwise c1 is kept.
953    *
954    *  This method is used to approximate a solution in one of the following cases
955    *
956    *     T1 & T2 <:< T3
957    *     T1 <:< T2 | T3
958    *
959    *  In the first case (the second one is analogous), we have a choice whether we
960    *  want to establish the subtyping judgement using
961    *
962    *     T1 <:< T3   or    T2 <:< T3
963    *
964    *  as a precondition. Either precondition might constrain type variables.
965    *  The purpose of this method is to pick the precondition that constrains less.
966    *  The method is not complete, because sometimes there is no best solution. Example:
967    *
968    *     A? & B?  <:  T
969    *
970    *  Here, each precondition leads to a different constraint, and neither of
971    *  the two post-constraints subsumes the other.
972    */
973   private def either(op1: => Boolean, op2: => Boolean): Boolean = {
974     val preConstraint = constraint
975     op1 && {
976       val leftConstraint = constraint
977       constraint = preConstraint
978       if (!(op2 && subsumes(leftConstraint, constraint, preConstraint))) {
979         if (constr != noPrinter && !subsumes(constraint, leftConstraint, preConstraint))
980           constr.println(i"CUT - prefer $leftConstraint over $constraint")
981         constraint = leftConstraint
982       }
983       true
984     } || op2
985   }
986 
987   /** Does type `tp1` have a member with name `name` whose normalized type is a subtype of
988    *  the normalized type of the refinement `tp2`?
989    *  Normalization is as follows: If `tp2` contains a skolem to its refinement type,
990    *  rebase both itself and the member info of `tp` on a freshly created skolem type.
991    */
992   protected def hasMatchingMember(name: Name, tp1: Type, tp2: RefinedType): Boolean =
993     /*>|>*/ trace(i"hasMatchingMember($tp1 . $name :? ${tp2.refinedInfo}), mbr: ${tp1.member(name).info}", subtyping) /*<|<*/ {
994       val rinfo2 = tp2.refinedInfo
995 
996       // If the member is an abstract type, compare the member itself
997       // instead of its bounds. This case is needed situations like:
998       //
999       //    class C { type T }
1000       //    val foo: C
1001       //    foo.type <: C { type T {= , <: , >:} foo.T }
1002       //
1003       // or like:
1004       //
1005       //    class C[T]
1006       //    C[_] <: C[TV]
1007       //
1008       // where TV is a type variable. See i2397.scala for an example of the latter.
1009       def matchAbstractTypeMember(info1: Type) = info1 match {
1010         case TypeBounds(lo, hi) if lo ne hi =>
1011           tp2.refinedInfo match {
1012             case rinfo2: TypeBounds =>
1013               val ref1 = tp1.widenExpr.select(name)
1014               isSubType(rinfo2.lo, ref1) && isSubType(ref1, rinfo2.hi)
1015             case _ =>
1016               false
1017           }
1018         case _ => false
1019       }
1020 
1021       def qualifies(m: SingleDenotation) =
1022         isSubType(m.info, rinfo2) || matchAbstractTypeMember(m.info)
1023 
1024       tp1.member(name) match { // inlined hasAltWith for performance
1025         case mbr: SingleDenotation => qualifies(mbr)
1026         case mbr => mbr hasAltWith qualifies
1027       }
1028     }
1029 
1030   final def ensureStableSingleton(tp: Type): SingletonType = tp.stripTypeVar match {
1031     case tp: SingletonType if tp.isStable => tp
1032     case tp: ValueType => SkolemType(tp)
1033     case tp: TypeProxy => ensureStableSingleton(tp.underlying)
1034   }
1035 
1036   /** Skip refinements in `tp2` which match corresponding refinements in `tp1`.
1037    *  "Match" means:
1038    *   - they appear in the same order,
1039    *   - they refine the same names,
1040    *   - the refinement in `tp1` is an alias type, and
1041    *   - neither refinement refers back to the refined type via a refined this.
1042    *  @return  The parent type of `tp2` after skipping the matching refinements.
1043    */
1044   private def skipMatching(tp1: Type, tp2: RefinedType): Type = tp1 match {
1045     case tp1 @ RefinedType(parent1, name1, rinfo1: TypeAlias) if name1 == tp2.refinedName =>
1046       tp2.parent match {
1047         case parent2: RefinedType => skipMatching(parent1, parent2)
1048         case parent2 => parent2
1049       }
1050     case _ => tp2
1051   }
1052 
1053   /** Are refinements in `tp1` pairwise subtypes of the refinements of `tp2`
1054    *  up to parent type `limit`?
1055    *  @pre `tp1` has the necessary number of refinements, they are type aliases,
1056    *       and their names match the corresponding refinements in `tp2`.
1057    *       Further, no refinement refers back to the refined type via a refined this.
1058    *  The precondition is established by `skipMatching`.
1059    */
1060   private def isSubRefinements(tp1: RefinedType, tp2: RefinedType, limit: Type): Boolean = {
1061     def hasSubRefinement(tp1: RefinedType, refine2: Type): Boolean = {
1062       isSubType(tp1.refinedInfo, refine2) || {
1063         // last effort: try to adapt variances of higher-kinded types if this is sound.
1064         // TODO: Move this to eta-expansion?
1065         val adapted2 = refine2.adaptHkVariances(tp1.parent.member(tp1.refinedName).symbol.info)
1066         adapted2.ne(refine2) && hasSubRefinement(tp1, adapted2)
1067       }
1068     }
1069     hasSubRefinement(tp1, tp2.refinedInfo) && (
1070       (tp2.parent eq limit) ||
1071       isSubRefinements(
1072         tp1.parent.asInstanceOf[RefinedType], tp2.parent.asInstanceOf[RefinedType], limit))
1073   }
1074 
1075   /** A type has been covered previously in subtype checking if it
1076    *  is some combination of TypeRefs that point to classes, where the
1077    *  combiners are AppliedTypes, RefinedTypes, RecTypes, And/Or-Types or AnnotatedTypes.
1078    */
1079    private def isCovered(tp: Type): Boolean = tp.dealias.stripTypeVar match {
1080     case tp: TypeRef => tp.symbol.isClass && tp.symbol != NothingClass && tp.symbol != NullClass
1081     case tp: AppliedType => isCovered(tp.tycon)
1082     case tp: RefinedOrRecType => isCovered(tp.parent)
1083     case tp: AnnotatedType => isCovered(tp.underlying)
1084     case tp: AndOrType => isCovered(tp.tp1) && isCovered(tp.tp2)
1085     case _ => false
1086   }
1087 
1088   /** Defer constraining type variables when compared against prototypes */
1089   def isMatchedByProto(proto: ProtoType, tp: Type) = tp.stripTypeVar match {
1090     case tp: TypeParamRef if constraint contains tp => true
1091     case _ => proto.isMatchedBy(tp)
1092   }
1093 
1094   /** Narrow gadt.bounds for the type parameter referenced by `tr` to include
1095    *  `bound` as an upper or lower bound (which depends on `isUpper`).
1096    *  Test that the resulting bounds are still satisfiable.
1097    */
1098   private def narrowGADTBounds(tr: NamedType, bound: Type, approx: ApproxState, isUpper: Boolean): Boolean = {
1099     val boundImprecise = if (isUpper) approx.high else approx.low
1100     ctx.mode.is(Mode.GADTflexible) && !frozenConstraint && !boundImprecise && {
1101       val tparam = tr.symbol
1102       gadts.println(i"narrow gadt bound of $tparam: ${tparam.info} from ${if (isUpper) "above" else "below"} to $bound ${bound.toString} ${bound.isRef(tparam)}")
1103       if (bound.isRef(tparam)) false
1104       else {
1105         val oldBounds = ctx.gadt.bounds(tparam)
1106         val newBounds =
1107           if (isUpper) TypeBounds(oldBounds.lo, oldBounds.hi & bound)
1108           else TypeBounds(oldBounds.lo | bound, oldBounds.hi)
1109         isSubType(newBounds.lo, newBounds.hi) &&
1110           { ctx.gadt.setBounds(tparam, newBounds); true }
1111       }
1112     }
1113   }
1114 
1115   // Tests around `matches`
1116 
1117   /** A function implementing `tp1` matches `tp2`. */
1118   final def matchesType(tp1: Type, tp2: Type, relaxed: Boolean): Boolean = tp1.widen match {
1119     case tp1: MethodType =>
1120       tp2.widen match {
1121         case tp2: MethodType =>
1122           // implicitness is ignored when matching
1123           matchingParams(tp1, tp2) &&
1124           matchesType(tp1.resultType, tp2.resultType.subst(tp2, tp1), relaxed)
1125         case tp2 =>
1126           relaxed && tp1.paramNames.isEmpty &&
1127             matchesType(tp1.resultType, tp2, relaxed)
1128       }
1129     case tp1: PolyType =>
1130       tp2.widen match {
1131         case tp2: PolyType =>
1132           sameLength(tp1.paramNames, tp2.paramNames) &&
1133           matchesType(tp1.resultType, tp2.resultType.subst(tp2, tp1), relaxed)
1134         case _ =>
1135           false
1136       }
1137     case _ =>
1138       tp2.widen match {
1139         case _: PolyType =>
1140           false
1141         case tp2: MethodType =>
1142           relaxed && tp2.paramNames.isEmpty &&
1143             matchesType(tp1, tp2.resultType, relaxed)
1144         case tp2 =>
1145           relaxed || isSameType(tp1, tp2)
1146       }
1147   }
1148 
1149   /** Do lambda types `lam1` and `lam2` have parameters that have the same types
1150    *  and the same implicit status? (after renaming one set to the other)
1151    */
1152   def matchingParams(lam1: MethodOrPoly, lam2: MethodOrPoly): Boolean = {
1153     /** Are `syms1` and `syms2` parameter lists with pairwise equivalent types? */
1154     def loop(formals1: List[Type], formals2: List[Type]): Boolean = formals1 match {
1155       case formal1 :: rest1 =>
1156         formals2 match {
1157           case formal2 :: rest2 =>
1158             val formal2a = if (lam2.isParamDependent) formal2.subst(lam2, lam1) else formal2
1159             (isSameTypeWhenFrozen(formal1, formal2a)
1160             || lam1.isJavaMethod && (formal2 isRef ObjectClass) && (formal1 isRef AnyClass)
1161             || lam2.isJavaMethod && (formal1 isRef ObjectClass) && (formal2 isRef AnyClass)) &&
1162             loop(rest1, rest2)
1163           case nil =>
1164             false
1165         }
1166       case nil =>
1167         formals2.isEmpty
1168     }
1169     loop(lam1.paramInfos, lam2.paramInfos)
1170   }
1171 
1172   // Type equality =:=
1173 
1174   /** Two types are the same if are mutual subtypes of each other */
1175   def isSameType(tp1: Type, tp2: Type): Boolean =
1176     if (tp1 eq NoType) false
1177     else if (tp1 eq tp2) true
1178     else isSubType(tp1, tp2) && isSubType(tp2, tp1)
1179 
1180   /** Same as `isSameType` but also can be applied to overloaded TermRefs, where
1181    *  two overloaded refs are the same if they have pairwise equal alternatives
1182    */
1183   def isSameRef(tp1: Type, tp2: Type): Boolean = trace(s"isSameRef($tp1, $tp2") {
1184     def isSubRef(tp1: Type, tp2: Type): Boolean = tp1 match {
1185       case tp1: TermRef if tp1.isOverloaded =>
1186         tp1.alternatives forall (isSubRef(_, tp2))
1187       case _ =>
1188         tp2 match {
1189           case tp2: TermRef if tp2.isOverloaded =>
1190             tp2.alternatives exists (isSubRef(tp1, _))
1191           case _ =>
1192             isSubType(tp1, tp2)
1193         }
1194     }
1195     isSubRef(tp1, tp2) && isSubRef(tp2, tp1)
1196   }
1197 
1198   /** The greatest lower bound of two types */
1199   def glb(tp1: Type, tp2: Type): Type = /*>|>*/ trace(s"glb(${tp1.show}, ${tp2.show})", subtyping, show = true) /*<|<*/ {
1200     if (tp1 eq tp2) tp1
1201     else if (!tp1.exists) tp2
1202     else if (!tp2.exists) tp1
1203     else if ((tp1 isRef AnyClass) || (tp2 isRef NothingClass)) tp2
1204     else if ((tp2 isRef AnyClass) || (tp1 isRef NothingClass)) tp1
1205     else tp2 match {  // normalize to disjunctive normal form if possible.
1206       case OrType(tp21, tp22) =>
1207         tp1 & tp21 | tp1 & tp22
1208       case _ =>
1209         tp1 match {
1210           case OrType(tp11, tp12) =>
1211             tp11 & tp2 | tp12 & tp2
1212           case _ =>
1213             val tp1a = dropIfSuper(tp1, tp2)
1214             if (tp1a ne tp1) glb(tp1a, tp2)
1215             else {
1216               val tp2a = dropIfSuper(tp2, tp1)
1217               if (tp2a ne tp2) glb(tp1, tp2a)
1218               else tp1 match {
1219                 case tp1: ConstantType =>
1220                   tp2 match {
1221                     case tp2: ConstantType =>
1222                       // Make use of the fact that the intersection of two constant types
1223                       // types which are not subtypes of each other is known to be empty.
1224                       // Note: The same does not apply to singleton types in general.
1225                       // E.g. we could have a pattern match against `x.type & y.type`
1226                       // which might succeed if `x` and `y` happen to be the same ref
1227                       // at run time. It would not work to replace that with `Nothing`.
1228                       // However, maybe we can still apply the replacement to
1229                       // types which are not explicitly written.
1230                       defn.NothingType
1231                     case _ => andType(tp1, tp2)
1232                   }
1233                 case _ => andType(tp1, tp2)
1234               }
1235           }
1236         }
1237     }
1238   }
1239 
1240   /** The greatest lower bound of a list types */
1241   final def glb(tps: List[Type]): Type =
1242     ((defn.AnyType: Type) /: tps)(glb)
1243 
1244   /** The least upper bound of two types
1245    *  @param canConstrain  If true, new constraints might be added to simplify the lub.
1246    *  @note  We do not admit singleton types in or-types as lubs.
1247    */
1248   def lub(tp1: Type, tp2: Type, canConstrain: Boolean = false): Type = /*>|>*/ trace(s"lub(${tp1.show}, ${tp2.show}, canConstrain=$canConstrain)", subtyping, show = true) /*<|<*/ {
1249     if (tp1 eq tp2) tp1
1250     else if (!tp1.exists) tp1
1251     else if (!tp2.exists) tp2
1252     else if ((tp1 isRef AnyClass) || (tp2 isRef NothingClass)) tp1
1253     else if ((tp2 isRef AnyClass) || (tp1 isRef NothingClass)) tp2
1254     else {
1255       val t1 = mergeIfSuper(tp1, tp2, canConstrain)
1256       if (t1.exists) t1
1257       else {
1258         val t2 = mergeIfSuper(tp2, tp1, canConstrain)
1259         if (t2.exists) t2
1260         else {
1261           val tp1w = tp1.widen
1262           val tp2w = tp2.widen
1263           if ((tp1 ne tp1w) || (tp2 ne tp2w)) lub(tp1w, tp2w)
1264           else orType(tp1w, tp2w) // no need to check subtypes again
1265         }
1266       }
1267     }
1268   }
1269 
1270   /** The least upper bound of a list of types */
1271   final def lub(tps: List[Type]): Type =
1272     ((defn.NothingType: Type) /: tps)(lub(_,_, canConstrain = false))
1273 
1274   /** Try to produce joint arguments for a lub `A[T_1, ..., T_n] | A[T_1', ..., T_n']` using
1275    *  the following strategies:
1276    *
1277    *    - if arguments are the same, that argument.
1278    *    - if corresponding parameter variance is co/contra-variant, the lub/glb.
1279    *    - otherwise a TypeBounds containing both arguments
1280    */
1281   def lubArgs(args1: List[Type], args2: List[Type], tparams: List[TypeParamInfo], canConstrain: Boolean = false): List[Type] =
1282     tparams match {
1283       case tparam :: tparamsRest =>
1284         val arg1 :: args1Rest = args1
1285         val arg2 :: args2Rest = args2
1286         val v = tparam.paramVariance
1287         val lubArg =
1288           if (isSameTypeWhenFrozen(arg1, arg2)) arg1
1289           else if (v > 0) lub(arg1.hiBound, arg2.hiBound, canConstrain)
1290           else if (v < 0) glb(arg1.loBound, arg2.loBound)
1291           else TypeBounds(glb(arg1.loBound, arg2.loBound),
1292                           lub(arg1.hiBound, arg2.hiBound, canConstrain))
1293         lubArg :: lubArgs(args1Rest, args2Rest, tparamsRest, canConstrain)
1294       case nil =>
1295         Nil
1296     }
1297 
1298   /** Try to produce joint arguments for a glb `A[T_1, ..., T_n] & A[T_1', ..., T_n']` using
1299    *  the following strategies:
1300    *
1301    *    - if arguments are the same, that argument.
1302    *    - if corresponding parameter variance is co/contra-variant, the glb/lub.
1303    *    - if at least one of the arguments if a TypeBounds, the union of
1304    *      the bounds.
1305    *    - if homogenizeArgs is set, and arguments can be unified by instantiating
1306    *      type parameters, the unified argument.
1307    *    - otherwise NoType
1308    *
1309    *  The unification rule is contentious because it cuts the constraint set.
1310    *  Therefore it is subject to Config option `alignArgsInAnd`.
1311    */
1312   def glbArgs(args1: List[Type], args2: List[Type], tparams: List[TypeParamInfo]): List[Type] =
1313     tparams match {
1314       case tparam :: tparamsRest =>
1315         val arg1 :: args1Rest = args1
1316         val arg2 :: args2Rest = args2
1317         val v = tparam.paramVariance
1318         val glbArg =
1319           if (isSameTypeWhenFrozen(arg1, arg2)) arg1
1320           else if (v > 0) glb(arg1.hiBound, arg2.hiBound)
1321           else if (v < 0) lub(arg1.loBound, arg2.loBound)
1322           else if (arg1.isInstanceOf[TypeBounds] || arg2.isInstanceOf[TypeBounds])
1323             TypeBounds(lub(arg1.loBound, arg2.loBound),
1324                        glb(arg1.hiBound, arg2.hiBound))
1325           else if (homogenizeArgs && !frozenConstraint && isSameType(arg1, arg2)) arg1
1326           else NoType
1327         glbArg :: glbArgs(args1Rest, args2Rest, tparamsRest)
1328       case nil =>
1329         Nil
1330     }
1331 
1332   private def recombineAndOr(tp: AndOrType, tp1: Type, tp2: Type) =
1333     if (!tp1.exists) tp2
1334     else if (!tp2.exists) tp1
1335     else tp.derivedAndOrType(tp1, tp2)
1336 
1337   /** If some (&-operand of) this type is a supertype of `sub` replace it with `NoType`.
1338    */
1339   private def dropIfSuper(tp: Type, sub: Type): Type =
1340     if (isSubTypeWhenFrozen(sub, tp)) NoType
1341     else tp match {
1342       case tp @ AndType(tp1, tp2) =>
1343         recombineAndOr(tp, dropIfSuper(tp1, sub), dropIfSuper(tp2, sub))
1344       case _ =>
1345         tp
1346     }
1347 
1348   /** Merge `t1` into `tp2` if t1 is a subtype of some &-summand of tp2.
1349    */
1350   private def mergeIfSub(tp1: Type, tp2: Type): Type =
1351     if (isSubTypeWhenFrozen(tp1, tp2))
1352       if (isSubTypeWhenFrozen(tp2, tp1)) tp2 else tp1 // keep existing type if possible
1353     else tp2 match {
1354       case tp2 @ AndType(tp21, tp22) =>
1355         val lower1 = mergeIfSub(tp1, tp21)
1356         if (lower1 eq tp21) tp2
1357         else if (lower1.exists) lower1 & tp22
1358         else {
1359           val lower2 = mergeIfSub(tp1, tp22)
1360           if (lower2 eq tp22) tp2
1361           else if (lower2.exists) tp21 & lower2
1362           else NoType
1363         }
1364       case _ =>
1365         NoType
1366     }
1367 
1368   /** Merge `tp1` into `tp2` if tp1 is a supertype of some |-summand of tp2.
1369    *  @param canConstrain  If true, new constraints might be added to make the merge possible.
1370    */
1371   private def mergeIfSuper(tp1: Type, tp2: Type, canConstrain: Boolean): Type =
1372     if (isSubType(tp2, tp1, whenFrozen = !canConstrain))
1373       if (isSubType(tp1, tp2, whenFrozen = !canConstrain)) tp2 else tp1 // keep existing type if possible
1374     else tp2 match {
1375       case tp2 @ OrType(tp21, tp22) =>
1376         val higher1 = mergeIfSuper(tp1, tp21, canConstrain)
1377         if (higher1 eq tp21) tp2
1378         else if (higher1.exists) higher1 | tp22
1379         else {
1380           val higher2 = mergeIfSuper(tp1, tp22, canConstrain)
1381           if (higher2 eq tp22) tp2
1382           else if (higher2.exists) tp21 | higher2
1383           else NoType
1384         }
1385       case _ =>
1386         NoType
1387     }
1388 
1389   /** Form a normalized conjunction of two types.
1390    *  Note: For certain types, `&` is distributed inside the type. This holds for
1391    *  all types which are not value types (e.g. TypeBounds, ClassInfo,
1392    *  ExprType, LambdaType). Also, when forming an `&`,
1393    *  instantiated TypeVars are dereferenced and annotations are stripped.
1394    *  Finally, refined types with the same refined name are
1395    *  opportunistically merged.
1396    *
1397    *  Sometimes, the conjunction of two types cannot be formed because
1398    *  the types are in conflict of each other. In particular:
1399    *
1400    *    1. Two different class types are conflicting.
1401    *    2. A class type conflicts with a type bounds that does not include the class reference.
1402    *    3. Two method or poly types with different (type) parameters but the same
1403    *       signature are conflicting
1404    *
1405    *  In these cases, a MergeError is thrown.
1406    */
1407   final def andType(tp1: Type, tp2: Type, erased: Boolean = ctx.erasedTypes) = trace(s"glb(${tp1.show}, ${tp2.show})", subtyping, show = true) {
1408     val t1 = distributeAnd(tp1, tp2)
1409     if (t1.exists) t1
1410     else {
1411       val t2 = distributeAnd(tp2, tp1)
1412       if (t2.exists) t2
1413       else if (erased) erasedGlb(tp1, tp2, isJava = false)
1414       else liftIfHK(tp1, tp2, AndType(_, _), _ & _)
1415     }
1416   }
1417 
1418   /** Form a normalized conjunction of two types.
1419    *  Note: For certain types, `|` is distributed inside the type. This holds for
1420    *  all types which are not value types (e.g. TypeBounds, ClassInfo,
1421    *  ExprType, LambdaType). Also, when forming an `|`,
1422    *  instantiated TypeVars are dereferenced and annotations are stripped.
1423    *
1424    *  Sometimes, the disjunction of two types cannot be formed because
1425    *  the types are in conflict of each other. (@see `andType` for an enumeration
1426    *  of these cases). In cases of conflict a `MergeError` is raised.
1427    *
1428    *  @param erased   Apply erasure semantics. If erased is true, instead of creating
1429    *                  an OrType, the lub will be computed using TypeCreator#erasedLub.
1430    */
1431   final def orType(tp1: Type, tp2: Type, erased: Boolean = ctx.erasedTypes) = {
1432     val t1 = distributeOr(tp1, tp2)
1433     if (t1.exists) t1
1434     else {
1435       val t2 = distributeOr(tp2, tp1)
1436       if (t2.exists) t2
1437       else if (erased) erasedLub(tp1, tp2)
1438       else liftIfHK(tp1, tp2, OrType(_, _), _ | _)
1439     }
1440   }
1441 
1442   /** `op(tp1, tp2)` unless `tp1` and `tp2` are type-constructors.
1443    *  In the latter case, combine `tp1` and `tp2` under a type lambda like this:
1444    *
1445    *    [X1, ..., Xn] -> op(tp1[X1, ..., Xn], tp2[X1, ..., Xn])
1446    */
1447   private def liftIfHK(tp1: Type, tp2: Type, op: (Type, Type) => Type, original: (Type, Type) => Type) = {
1448     val tparams1 = tp1.typeParams
1449     val tparams2 = tp2.typeParams
1450     def applied(tp: Type) = tp.appliedTo(tp.typeParams.map(_.paramInfoAsSeenFrom(tp)))
1451     if (tparams1.isEmpty)
1452       if (tparams2.isEmpty) op(tp1, tp2)
1453       else original(tp1, applied(tp2))
1454     else if (tparams2.isEmpty)
1455       original(applied(tp1), tp2)
1456     else if (tparams1.hasSameLengthAs(tparams2))
1457       HKTypeLambda(
1458         paramNames = (HKTypeLambda.syntheticParamNames(tparams1.length), tparams1, tparams2)
1459           .zipped.map((pname, tparam1, tparam2) =>
1460             pname.withVariance((tparam1.paramVariance + tparam2.paramVariance) / 2)))(
1461         paramInfosExp = tl => (tparams1, tparams2).zipped.map((tparam1, tparam2) =>
1462           tl.integrate(tparams1, tparam1.paramInfoAsSeenFrom(tp1)).bounds &
1463           tl.integrate(tparams2, tparam2.paramInfoAsSeenFrom(tp2)).bounds),
1464         resultTypeExp = tl =>
1465           original(tp1.appliedTo(tl.paramRefs), tp2.appliedTo(tl.paramRefs)))
1466     else original(applied(tp1), applied(tp2))
1467   }
1468 
1469   /** Try to distribute `&` inside type, detect and handle conflicts
1470    *  @pre !(tp1 <: tp2) && !(tp2 <:< tp1) -- these cases were handled before
1471    */
1472   private def distributeAnd(tp1: Type, tp2: Type): Type = tp1 match {
1473     case tp1 @ AppliedType(tycon1, args1) =>
1474       tp2 match {
1475         case AppliedType(tycon2, args2)
1476         if tycon1.typeSymbol == tycon2.typeSymbol && tycon1 =:= tycon2 =>
1477           val jointArgs = glbArgs(args1, args2, tycon1.typeParams)
1478           if (jointArgs.forall(_.exists)) (tycon1 & tycon2).appliedTo(jointArgs)
1479           else NoType
1480         case _ =>
1481           NoType
1482       }
1483     // opportunistically merge same-named refinements
1484     // this does not change anything semantically (i.e. merging or not merging
1485     // gives =:= types), but it keeps the type smaller.
1486     case tp1: RefinedType =>
1487       tp2 match {
1488         case tp2: RefinedType if tp1.refinedName == tp2.refinedName =>
1489           tp1.derivedRefinedType(tp1.parent & tp2.parent, tp1.refinedName,
1490             tp1.refinedInfo & tp2.refinedInfo)
1491         case _ =>
1492           NoType
1493       }
1494     case tp1: RecType =>
1495       tp1.rebind(distributeAnd(tp1.parent, tp2))
1496     case ExprType(rt1) =>
1497       tp2 match {
1498         case ExprType(rt2) =>
1499           ExprType(rt1 & rt2)
1500         case _ =>
1501           rt1 & tp2
1502       }
1503     case tp1: TypeVar if tp1.isInstantiated =>
1504       tp1.underlying & tp2
1505     case tp1: AnnotatedType =>
1506       tp1.underlying & tp2
1507     case _ =>
1508       NoType
1509   }
1510 
1511   /** Try to distribute `|` inside type, detect and handle conflicts
1512    *  Note that, unlike for `&`, a disjunction cannot be pushed into
1513    *  a refined or applied type. Example:
1514    *
1515    *     List[T] | List[U] is not the same as List[T | U].
1516    *
1517    *  The rhs is a proper supertype of the lhs.
1518    */
1519   private def distributeOr(tp1: Type, tp2: Type): Type = tp1 match {
1520     case ExprType(rt1) =>
1521       ExprType(rt1 | tp2.widenExpr)
1522     case tp1: TypeVar if tp1.isInstantiated =>
1523       tp1.underlying | tp2
1524     case tp1: AnnotatedType =>
1525       tp1.underlying | tp2
1526     case _ =>
1527       NoType
1528   }
1529 
1530   /** Show type, handling type types better than the default */
1531   private def showType(tp: Type)(implicit ctx: Context) = tp match {
1532     case ClassInfo(_, cls, _, _, _) => cls.showLocated
1533     case bounds: TypeBounds => "type bounds" + bounds.show
1534     case _ => tp.show
1535   }
1536 
1537   /** A comparison function to pick a winner in case of a merge conflict */
1538   private def isAsGood(tp1: Type, tp2: Type): Boolean = tp1 match {
1539     case tp1: ClassInfo =>
1540       tp2 match {
1541         case tp2: ClassInfo =>
1542           isSubTypeWhenFrozen(tp1.prefix, tp2.prefix) || (tp1.cls.owner derivesFrom tp2.cls.owner)
1543         case _ =>
1544           false
1545       }
1546     case tp1: PolyType =>
1547       tp2 match {
1548         case tp2: PolyType =>
1549           tp1.typeParams.length == tp2.typeParams.length &&
1550           isAsGood(tp1.resultType, tp2.resultType.subst(tp2, tp1))
1551         case _ =>
1552           false
1553       }
1554     case tp1: MethodType =>
1555       tp2 match {
1556         case tp2: MethodType =>
1557           def asGoodParams(formals1: List[Type], formals2: List[Type]) =
1558             (formals2 corresponds formals1)(isSubTypeWhenFrozen)
1559           asGoodParams(tp1.paramInfos, tp2.paramInfos) &&
1560           (!asGoodParams(tp2.paramInfos, tp1.paramInfos) ||
1561            isAsGood(tp1.resultType, tp2.resultType))
1562         case _ =>
1563           false
1564       }
1565     case _ =>
1566       false
1567   }
1568 
1569   /** A new type comparer of the same type as this one, using the given context. */
1570   def copyIn(ctx: Context) = new TypeComparer(ctx)
1571 
1572   // ----------- Diagnostics --------------------------------------------------
1573 
1574   /** A hook for showing subtype traces. Overridden in ExplainingTypeComparer */
1575   def traceIndented[T](str: String)(op: => T): T = op
1576 
1577   private def traceInfo(tp1: Type, tp2: Type) =
1578     s"${tp1.show} <:< ${tp2.show}" + {
1579       if (ctx.settings.verbose.value || Config.verboseExplainSubtype) {
1580         s" ${tp1.getClass}, ${tp2.getClass}" +
1581         (if (frozenConstraint) " frozen" else "") +
1582         (if (ctx.mode is Mode.TypevarsMissContext) " tvars-miss-ctx" else "")
1583       }
1584       else ""
1585     }
1586 
1587   /** Show subtype goal that led to an assertion failure */
1588   def showGoal(tp1: Type, tp2: Type)(implicit ctx: Context) = {
1589     println(i"assertion failure for ${show(tp1)} <:< ${show(tp2)}, frozen = $frozenConstraint")
1590     def explainPoly(tp: Type) = tp match {
1591       case tp: TypeParamRef => ctx.echo(s"TypeParamRef ${tp.show} found in ${tp.binder.show}")
1592       case tp: TypeRef if tp.symbol.exists => ctx.echo(s"typeref ${tp.show} found in ${tp.symbol.owner.show}")
1593       case tp: TypeVar => ctx.echo(s"typevar ${tp.show}, origin = ${tp.origin}")
1594       case _ => ctx.echo(s"${tp.show} is a ${tp.getClass}")
1595     }
1596     if (Config.verboseExplainSubtype) {
1597       explainPoly(tp1)
1598       explainPoly(tp2)
1599     }
1600   }
1601 
1602   /** Record statistics about the total number of subtype checks
1603    *  and the number of "successful" subtype checks, i.e. checks
1604    *  that form part of a subtype derivation tree that's ultimately successful.
1605    */
1606   def recordStatistics(result: Boolean, prevSuccessCount: Int) = {
1607     // Stats.record(s"isSubType ${tp1.show} <:< ${tp2.show}")
1608     totalCount += 1
1609     if (result) successCount += 1 else successCount = prevSuccessCount
1610     if (recCount == 0) {
1611       Stats.record("successful subType", successCount)
1612       Stats.record("total subType", totalCount)
1613       successCount = 0
1614       totalCount = 0
1615     }
1616   }
1617 }
1618 
1619 object TypeComparer {
1620 
1621   private[core] def show(res: Any)(implicit ctx: Context) = res match {
1622     case res: printing.Showable if !ctx.settings.YexplainLowlevel.value => res.show
1623     case _ => String.valueOf(res)
1624   }
1625 
1626   private val LoApprox = 1
1627   private val HiApprox = 2
1628 
1629   class ApproxState(private val bits: Int) extends AnyVal {
1630     override def toString = {
1631       val lo = if ((bits & LoApprox) != 0) "LoApprox" else ""
1632       val hi = if ((bits & HiApprox) != 0) "HiApprox" else ""
1633       lo ++ hi
1634     }
1635     def addLow = new ApproxState(bits | LoApprox)
1636     def addHigh = new ApproxState(bits | HiApprox)
1637     def low = (bits & LoApprox) != 0
1638     def high = (bits & HiApprox) != 0
1639   }
1640 
1641   val NoApprox = new ApproxState(0)
1642 
1643   /** Show trace of comparison operations when performing `op` as result string */
1644   def explained[T](op: Context => T)(implicit ctx: Context): String = {
1645     val nestedCtx = ctx.fresh.setTypeComparerFn(new ExplainingTypeComparer(_))
1646     op(nestedCtx)
1647     nestedCtx.typeComparer.toString
1648   }
1649 }
1650 
1651 /** A type comparer that can record traces of subtype operations */
1652 class ExplainingTypeComparer(initctx: Context) extends TypeComparer(initctx) {
1653   import TypeComparer._
1654 
1655   private[this] var indent = 0
1656   private val b = new StringBuilder
1657 
1658   private[this] var skipped = false
1659 
1660   override def traceIndented[T](str: String)(op: => T): T =
1661     if (skipped) op
1662     else {
1663       indent += 2
1664       b append "\n" append (" " * indent) append "==> " append str
1665       val res = op
1666       b append "\n" append (" " * indent) append "<== " append str append " = " append show(res)
1667       indent -= 2
1668       res
1669     }
1670 
1671   override def isSubType(tp1: Type, tp2: Type, approx: ApproxState) =
1672     traceIndented(s"${show(tp1)} <:< ${show(tp2)}${if (Config.verboseExplainSubtype) s" ${tp1.getClass} ${tp2.getClass}" else ""} $approx ${if (frozenConstraint) " frozen" else ""}") {
1673       super.isSubType(tp1, tp2, approx)
1674     }
1675 
1676   override def hasMatchingMember(name: Name, tp1: Type, tp2: RefinedType): Boolean =
1677     traceIndented(s"hasMatchingMember(${show(tp1)} . $name, ${show(tp2.refinedInfo)}), member = ${show(tp1.member(name).info)}") {
1678       super.hasMatchingMember(name, tp1, tp2)
1679     }
1680 
1681   override def lub(tp1: Type, tp2: Type, canConstrain: Boolean = false) =
1682     traceIndented(s"lub(${show(tp1)}, ${show(tp2)}, canConstrain=$canConstrain)") {
1683       super.lub(tp1, tp2, canConstrain)
1684     }
1685 
1686   override def glb(tp1: Type, tp2: Type) =
1687     traceIndented(s"glb(${show(tp1)}, ${show(tp2)})") {
1688       super.glb(tp1, tp2)
1689     }
1690 
1691   override def addConstraint(param: TypeParamRef, bound: Type, fromBelow: Boolean): Boolean =
1692     traceIndented(i"add constraint $param ${if (fromBelow) ">:" else "<:"} $bound $frozenConstraint, constraint = ${ctx.typerState.constraint}") {
1693       super.addConstraint(param, bound, fromBelow)
1694     }
1695 
1696   override def copyIn(ctx: Context) = new ExplainingTypeComparer(ctx)
1697 
1698   override def toString = "Subtype trace:" + { try b.toString finally b.clear() }
1699 }
